Semi-Human Cook:  Writing your book is going to rip you up a little bit.  A sort of self induced implosive flooding.  It is really going to impact on some of our numbed out buddies and a lot of folks who want to &quot;know&quot; more about the truth. My adopted mom has her masters in English and did thirty one years in the trenches as an English teacher.  She is pretty sharp when it comes to Viet Nam.  Her only natural son, did a tour with B Company, 2d Battalion, 501st Infantry, 101st Air Borne Division.  James survived Hamburger Hill.  Mom is out of an old Quaker bunch and doesn't really thrive on violence, but she stands by James and I.<br>
If you need any help with editing etc... give me an email response.<br>
&quot;Hang in there... like a hair in a biscuit!&quot;<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  I don't know the guys who used to drop beer wrapped in the &quot;Stars and Stripes&quot; on Marines.  I used to fly over and drop deodorant wrapped in coloring books.
